    "name": "Screenshot Social API",
    "description": "Mobile-first API for the screenshot-sharing social platform.\n\n## Versioning strategy\nEach API version lives in its own top-level folder (`v1`, later `v2`, ...) with the version hardcoded into each request's path (e.g. `/v1/posts`). Existing versions are never modified once shipped.\n\nWhen v2 starts: duplicate the `v1` folder (right-click -> Duplicate), rename it to `v2`, then use Postman's collection-wide Find & Replace to swap `/v1/` -> `/v2/` inside the duplicated folder only. This keeps v1 and v2 requests runnable side by side in the same collection, matching how the API itself will serve both `/api/v1/...` and `/api/v2/...` concurrently.\n\n## Running this collection\nRequests are ordered so you can hit \"Run collection\" top to bottom:\n1. Register (sets `{{token}}` / `{{user_id}}` for Alice)\n2. Register (Second User) (sets `{{token_b}}` / `{{user_b_id}}` for Bob)\n3. Create Post is sent as Bob so there's something in Alice's feed once she follows him\n4. Everything else chains off `{{post_id}}` / `{{comment_id}}`, captured automatically by each request's Tests script\n\nSet the `base_url` collection variable to point at your environment (defaults to this project's local ServBay host).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://telm.test/api", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token_b", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_b_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "post_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "comment_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
